      <p>
        Zow Tlang is guarding the eastern horizon of Bangladesh and Myanmar
        border. In Bawm language the term Zow means Mizo (Mizo is derived from
        Mizoram, India. Probable reason is that Bangladesh was a part of greater
        India before 1947) and Tlang means Mountain. According to American and
        Russian topographic maps Zow Tlang is mentioned as Mowdok Mual. As per
