      <br />
      <br />
      <p>Although it is widely reported to be the highest point in Bangladesh at
        1,230 meters,recent SRTM data, GPS readings and Russian topographic
        mapping show that its true height is less than 1,000 meters. On the top
        of Keokradong there is a small shelter and a signboard put up by the
        Bangladeshi military proclaiming the altitude to be 3172 feet. Garmin
        GPS recorded 974 meters (3196 feet) at this location, a different team
        measured 986m with 3m accuracy by GPS,a measurement consistent with
        Russian topographic mapping and SRTM data. It is at 21°57′00″N
        92°30′53″E. USGS and Russian mapping dispute the claim that this is the
        location correctly named Keokradong; they show Keokradong at an 883m
        summit further north.
      </p>
